@startuml S3 Bucket Request Flow

title S3 Bucket Request Flow - Access Control Sequence

actor "User\n176.83.52.247/32" as User

box "AWS Account (us-east-1)" #LightYellow
  participant "S3 Bucket Policy\n(IP Validation)" as Policy
  participant "S3 Bucket\njorge-roldan-solutions-architect-\nexample-bucket" as S3
  participant "S3 Object\nhello-world.html" as Object
end box

== Successful Request Flow ==

User -> Policy: GetObject Request\n(HTTPS)
activate Policy

Policy -> Policy: Extract Source IP\nfrom Request

alt Source IP matches 176.83.52.247/32
  Policy -> Policy: Evaluate Policy\n✅ Allow
  Policy -> S3: Forward Request
  activate S3

  S3 -> Object: Retrieve Object
  activate Object
  Object --> S3: Return hello-world.html\n(text/html)
  deactivate Object

  S3 --> Policy: Object Data
  deactivate S3
  Policy --> User: 200 OK\n+ Object Content

else Source IP does NOT match
  Policy -> Policy: Evaluate Policy\n❌ Deny
  Policy --> User: 403 Forbidden\nAccess Denied
end

deactivate Policy

== Terraform State Management (Background) ==

note over S3
  Terraform state stored in:
  • S3: aws-solutions-architect-tf-states
  • DynamoDB: aws-solutions-architect-tf-states-locks
end note

@enduml
